a:5:{s:5:"title";s:43:"OpenCRM adds SMS scheduling to Email Plans";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:817:"<p>OpenCRM extended its Email Plans feature to include SMS/text messaging, allowing teams to schedule outbound messages to Leads and Contacts as part of timed outreach.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>Email Plans can now schedule:</p>
<ul>
<li>one SMS, or</li>
<li>a series of SMS messages</li>
</ul>
<p>SMS can be sent to Leads and Contacts.</p>
<p>##Why it matters</p>
<p>Teams already using Email Plans for timed follow-ups can now run SMS sequences through the same scheduling mechanism, reducing manual reminders and keeping outreach cadences consistent.</p>
<h3>More details</h3>
<p>OpenCRM points users to its Email Plans documentation for setup and usage.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://productupdates.opencrm.co.uk/en/news/392">https://productupdates.opencrm.co.uk/en/news/392</a></p>
